# Interface-Based Design with Factory Functions

**Pattern**: Export interfaces and factory functions. Keep classes as private implementation details.

## Do

```typescript
export interface CodecRegistry {
  get(id: string): unknown | undefined;
  register(codec: unknown): void;
}

export function createCodecRegistry(): CodecRegistry {
  return new CodecRegistryImpl();
}

class CodecRegistryImpl implements CodecRegistry {
  // ...
}
```

## Avoid

```typescript
// Avoid exporting concrete classes as the primary surface.
export class CodecRegistry {
  // ...
}
```

## Why this matters

- Keeps public APIs stable while allowing private implementation changes
- Makes mocking/testing easier (tests can target interfaces)
- Encourages “thin core, fat targets” and clean layering

